  "correctAnswer": "36",
  "section": "Math",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Set up",
      "content": "Translate the two given relationships into equations. &ldquo;42% of $h$ equals 54% of $j$&rdquo; gives $0.42h = 0.54j$, so $h = \\dfrac{54}{42}j$. &ldquo;$j$ is 28% of $k$&rdquo; gives $j = 0.28k$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve",
      "content": "Substitute $j = 0.28k$ into the expression for $h$: $$h = \\frac{54}{42} \\cdot 0.28k = \\frac{54 \\times 0.28}{42}k = \\frac{15.12}{42}k = 0.36k$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Answer",
      "content": "$h$ is 36% of $k$, so <strong>36</strong> is correct."
    }
  ]
}